		<button class="collapsible">Day 1 : Delhi – Vrindavan - Mathura</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>After your arrival at Delhi, you will be taken to Vrindavan, which is Lord Krishna’s childhood place. In Vrindavan, you can check out the Iskon Temple and then visit the Bankey Bihari Temple, Main temple of Lord Krishna. It is one of the oldest temples built in the year of 1921. Later, proceed to Rangaji Temple and the Vrindavan’s highest temple. Move to Mathura and get into the hotel. Enjoy a delicious meal and take rest at your leisure. In the evening, proceed to Mathura which is the birth place of Lord Krishna. Ensure to visit the Dwaraka Dhish Temple and gaze at the Yamuna ji “Maha Aarti”. Spend your overnight stay at Mathura.<p>
		</div>

		<button class="collapsible">Day 2 : Mathura - Gokul - Mahavan - Govardhan – Mathura</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Take your breakfast in the morning. Our tour representatives will drive you to Gokul and visit the Gokul Nath Ji Temple. Continue to visit Mahavan and ‘Assi Khambha’ the temple that is devoted to lord Krishna. You need to check out Govardhan, where Lord Krishna held aloft ‘Giriraj’, the stonework hill on his finger for seven days. Return back to Mathura for night stay at the hotel.</p>
		</div>

		<button class="collapsible">Day 3 : Mathura - Nandgaon - Barsana – Delhi</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>On this day, you will be visiting the Pan Sarovar. This lake is one of the distinguished lakes in Braj. Move on to Barsana - the birth place of Radha. Proceed to the water tank ‘Prem Sarovar’, the first meeting spot of Radha and Krishna. Later, get back to Delhi and move to your home.</p>
		</div><br><br><br><br><br>

